column8: text

PETALING JAYA: Defence Minister Datuk Seri Hishammuddin Hussein jumped into action to help a motorcyclist who was involved in an accident.An onlooker at the scene said the victim fell from his motorcycle and was seen lying on the road in pain."Suddenly, we saw Datuk Seri get out of his vehicle and made his way to the motorcyclist," the onlooker told The Star.The accident involved a motorcycle and a bicycle at a roundabout in Sembrong, Johor on Saturday.Hishammuddin was said to be on his way back to Kluang after a working visit at his constituency in Sembrong when the accident happened."Datuk Seri only left the scene after the motorcyclist said he was alright and could manage by himself," the onlooker added. - THE STAR
